{
  "page": "Lionstar",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Lionstar_by_Lukasz_Jaskolski.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e5/The_Lionstar_by_Lukasz_Jaskolski.jpg/400px-The_Lionstar_by_Lukasz_Jaskolski.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"280\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e5/The_Lionstar_by_Lukasz_Jaskolski.jpg/600px-The_Lionstar_by_Lukasz_Jaskolski.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e5/The_Lionstar_by_Lukasz_Jaskolski.jpg/800px-The_Lionstar_by_Lukasz_Jaskolski.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Lionstar_by_Lukasz_Jaskolski.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <i>Lionstar</i> - by Lukasz Jaskolski. © FFG</div></div></div>\n<p>The <i><b>Lionstar</b></i> is a war galley in service to the <a href=\"/index.php/Royal_fleet\" title=\"Royal fleet\">royal fleet</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Its hull is painted the black and gold of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"House Baratheon of King&#39;s Landing\">House Baratheon of King's Landing</a>, while its figurehead is a <a href=\"/index.php/Lion\" title=\"Lion\">lion</a> with an upraised paw.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lionstar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lionstar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <i>Lionstar</i> is part of the fleet <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> sends to bring <a href=\"/index.php/Myrcella_Baratheon\" title=\"Myrcella Baratheon\">Myrcella Baratheon</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>. The captains have orders to run off or destroy any lone ship they spot on the way. Should an enemy fleet attack, the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Bold_Wind\" title=\"Bold Wind\">Bold Wind</a></i> would escort the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Seaswift\" title=\"Seaswift\">Seaswift</a></i> while the rest of the fleet, consisting of <i><a href=\"/index.php/King_Robert%27s_Hammer\" title=\"King Robert&#39;s Hammer\">King Robert's Hammer</a></i>, <i>Lionstar</i>, and <i><a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Lyanna\" title=\"Lady Lyanna\">Lady Lyanna</a></i>, would give battle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When the fleet of <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> enters the <a href=\"/index.php/Blackwater_Rush\" title=\"Blackwater Rush\">Blackwater Rush</a> before the start of the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> notes the absence of the <i>Lionstar</i>, <i>King Robert's Hammer</i> and the <i>Lady Lyanna</i>, making him suspect a trap, as these ships should lead any defense of the enemy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lionstar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <i>Lionstar</i> transports <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Frey\" title=\"Rhaegar Frey\">Rhaegar</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jared_Frey\" title=\"Jared Frey\">Jared</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Symond_Frey\" title=\"Symond Frey\">Symond Frey</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a> to deliver the remains of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Wendel_Manderly\" title=\"Wendel Manderly\">Wendel Manderly</a>, who was killed at the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Red Wedding</a>, and to negotiate <a href=\"/index.php/House_Manderly\" title=\"House Manderly\">House Manderly</a> abandoning the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">northern</a> cause and bending the knee to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> and King <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen I Baratheon</a>. On the way, the ship makes a stop at <a href=\"/index.php/Sisterton\" title=\"Sisterton\">Sisterton</a> to fill its water casks and the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Frey\" title=\"House Frey\">Freys</a> are guests of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Godric_Borrell\" title=\"Godric Borrell\">Godric Borrell</a>. Godric informs Davos of this when the Onion Lord arrives in Sisterton twelve days later.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Davos hopes that the ship sank in the same storms that destroyed <a href=\"/index.php/Salladhor_Saan\" title=\"Salladhor Saan\">Salladhor Saan</a>'s fleet. However, when he arrives in White Harbor on board the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Merry_Midwife\" title=\"Merry Midwife\">Merry Midwife</a></i> to negotiate a possible alliance between Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a> and Stannis, Davos spots the <i>Lionstar</i> lying in the harbor. Its banner displays the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"House Baratheon of King&#39;s Landing\">Baratheon</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannister</a> arms of King <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen I</a>. This increases Davos's doubts whether he can succeed in his mission.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lionstar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_41\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 41\">Chapter 41</a>, Tyrion IX.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_15\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 15\">Chapter 15</a>, Davos II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_58\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 58\">Chapter 58</a>, Davos III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_9\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 9\">Chapter 9</a>, Davos I.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404122110\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.032 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.054 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 484/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8755/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1960/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 127/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 2454/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.010/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 4.52 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   42.527      1 -total\n 69.48%   29.547      1 Template:Italic_title\n 23.59%   10.034      6 Template:Ref\n 13.84%    5.887      6 Template:Ref/core\n  5.83%    2.479      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:3863-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404122110 and revision id 219066\n -->\n",
